body:
@rxin Thank you for your comment.
On a second thought, it's not good solution and I noticed the root cause of this issue is that FetchFailedException is not thrown when local fetch has failed.
https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/1578 may be better solution.

@mateiz We still do not have all of them, I think but some of them might not be very critical. They are mostly related to external/*. I can disable the modules for which those artifacts are missing only in the cross build for scala 2.11 specifically, they would still be available by scala 2.10 though. 
I can start working on this if you think its a priority. 

@avati You are welcome with your contribution, if you think you completed any of the subtask you can send a PR.
